{
  "stem": "4830.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "According to a law that was brought in Hungary in 1885 or '84, Jewish student-- if there was no Jewish school in that district where he lived-- had the right not to-- not to write on Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on my father's insistence, I had exercised this right, and I did not [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] write anything on Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I attended school, I listened, but I didn't write because that was not allowed according to Jewish law.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I would say that I came from a very traditional, very strong, religious family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it wasn't embarrassing to be at school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was embarrassing for me not to be able to write when all the others were writing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But since this was the rule, I observed this until it was possible to observe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had several confrontations as a result of that, as years were becoming more and more difficult.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With-- particularly with a teacher who was of German extraction, who in 1928-- just to characterize him-- Hungarized his name from [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Zippsel ?] to [INAUDIBLE], which is a Hungarian name, and in 1936 changed his name back to [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Zippsel ?] as Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he decided to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] make me write on Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, of course, I did not really obey him, and I quoted the law, that I have the right not to write.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his method was that he put first every-- he was teaching Hungarian and German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So every Hungarian paper that we had to write in class was on Saturdays and every German paper was on Saturdays.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at the end of first half of the trimester, he failed me in both subjects because I didn't write any of the papers.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
